rComments: The worst.

Professor Palmer made sure he made his class interesting.  He cares about all his students, if you need help, or just want more information he will find time to help!  This class was great would recommend it!

Prof Palmer is a really great guy ! Sometimes hard with the students but really nice in general. The final was really easy and simple. If you have the chance to take him in the ADM 1301 class just do it.
Avoid at all costs. Egotisitical, self aggrandizing, smug and passive aggressive. Exams contained far too much material that wasn't covered in the first place.

Unwilling to change group project marks if your peers rate you poorly even if you contributed heavily to the group project. Get a group that rates you otherwise you'll end up with a terrible mark you can't change. Long boring lectures and a weird format for the final exam.

Honestly, he may or may not be your cup of tea, it really depends on the type of learner you are. Apart from first year courses, he's an extremely easy grader on reports/presentations. His quizzes on the other hand can be a hit or miss because of oddly specific (and irrelevant) questions. He's pretty engaging and fun (loves to flex his life tho)

Class was online so I can't speak for the people who took him in-person, but his lectures and grade schemes were well planned and communicated properly. 

Lectures were tedious at times but he made them fun by asking questions, sharing stories and giving breaks.
dry, passive aggressive, switches up his "nice" personality after like week 3. don't believe the good comments/reviews on here, he writes them himself.

The one and only ADM1301 prof this semester, and he only gives you the choice to take this class from 7-9 in a -20 degree winter. Make the class unnecessarily hard to force you to pay attention to his class, but the lectures can hypnotize you to sleep. My high school teacher said only Ivey, Smith or Schulich can teach you something. She's right.

Honestly, I prof. Palmer's class was my first lecture in university ever. I walked out of there feeling motivated and happy to be there. However, as the semester progressed he began lacking empathy and being very passive aggressive with emails and even when you speak to him in person. He's okay but there are better profs for sure.

Really enjoyed the way he delivered the sometimes dry material. His funny anecdotes helped me focus during some long lectures. Make sure to read the whole textbook and watch all of the lectures before the exam, as there will be content not covered in the slides.

I really enjoyed the material of the class and the way Prof John delivered lectures. There was one essay, one group case study, and a final exam. The essay was graded harder than I had expected but it was still fair. He doesn't record his lectures so make sure to show up for class or you'll miss out on a lot of information. Overall, nice guy.
Graded more on written papers than tests. Cares about his students.
Avoid this prof. I did decent in the class but he is a really tough person to deal with and his expectations are not clear. Exam has nothing to do with the course.

Pretty chill guy. Lectures were easy to follow and he gave a lot of interesting examples. His lectures were a lot like having a conversation as opposed to listening to a presentation. Individual assignment was easy, just takes time & write exactly what the rubric says. There is also a group assignment and presentation which weren't too difficult

Prof Palmers lectures go so fast you physically do not have time to type the notes let alone write them. Your looking at 45-50 slides per class plus him insisting that reading the text is mandatory. The group project was used to lower mostly everyones grades when it should have been used to boost the grades of those that carried the team.

For this class, there was no midterm test, only an assignment and group project. The projects didn't reflect much of the course, and I felt I haven't learned much throughout the semester. He also tends to get off topic a lot, making it challenging to concentrate in his class. Don't recommend him.
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Prof Palmer is good. Attend his lectures (or watch recordings at x2) and you'll do fine. Individual Assignment was graded fairly. Group project was easy. His lectures could be half the time if the subject was taught with less personal opinion or stories, though did make the course interesting. Exam was standard but you have no idea what to focus on

I liked how instead of midterms we had assignments which honestly was so nice but I only wish that he gave us more exam prep questions cuz the exam wasn't too bad but going into it we had 0 idea what to even expect, except that it would basically cover every single thing we covered in the course. i also made the mistake of taking a 3 hr class AVOID

Palmer is NOT as bad as this year has been saying. High school students who weren't ready for a university course are the ones complaining. The group project was rough for sure-but all group projects are. If your group members actually like you and you do your work-then you'll be absolutely fine. Watch his lectures on 2x speed and you're set w John

He is the type of professor who may not have solved the problem right away, but he will make certain that all problems are resolved in the end. People are giving him one star because of the peer evaluation issue, which he has already resolved. TA for this class was 5 stars.

Doesnt like answering questions outside of class hours. Grading system inconsistent and unfair, plays the good prof. Reviews for important projects are non existent and grading system not fair. I personally will avoid this prof at all cost

John Palmer has to be the most egotistical person I've ever met. If he spent less time talking about himself his lectures might be a little shorter. He claims to care about his students but his condescending tone to students questions and concerns says otherwise. Few assignments/tests are given and they are all graded tough.

If you can take Palmer or Levasseur TAKE PALMER. To start, Palmer is alright he's not the best or the worst prof I've ever had. He makes lectures somewhat entertaining and he seems to teach the subject well. The group project peer evaluation is one of the stupidest metrics I've ever seen which lowered many peoples' marks. The exam was very random.

When emailing him outside of class he gets weirdly mad when you ask specific questions he doesn't like. The peer evaluation system on the group project was terrible lowered everyone's grade for no reason. The final exam had questions that weren't even taught and for exam review, we only got 3 questions for an exam worth 40% which is ridiculous.

Energetic in lectures but lacks in focus, boring, also rambles. Unclear and bad grading criteria for group project. Exam is designed to make you suffer and lose marks. Pace yourself for a 15-20 pg report that is marked without real consideration.

He's funny I'll give him that. His lectures are super heavy, so much info in the slideshows it is a copy of the textbook. He isn't super helpful when you ask questions about assignments. The group project is 30% of your grade so you better hope you have good teammates, the weight of peer evaluations is extreme. Some exam questions weren't taught

The group project ruined the whole course. confusing system, dropping my gpa. i have high 80s and 90s in every course and I understand the material so well for this class but the way its marked doesn't make any sense. very stressed and worried, don't know how I'm gonna do well now

Although he seems like a fun guy overall, his class is very stressful and lecture loaded. He doesnt give reviews or a proper outline for his exam and is a very tough marker for the individual project and group. The peer evaluation is a big mark in the mark which is bull and if something goes wrong in your presentation he doesnt stop the timer.

He was so bad, I wanted to give him a zero but that's not possible so I give him a 1. This teacher makes this class more complicated then it should be. He gives little to no information and is quick to deducts marks. If you have the possibility take this course with another teacher, you'll find it more easy. Also, no practice questions for final.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Don't take this prof he does not grade fairly at all. Get ready to lose marks over the smallest things. I asked him to regrade my paper and he reduced my mark by 15% even though I followed everything on the rubric. The prof talks too much about himself and useless examples in class. Very long lectures and hard to stay focused bc of boring material.

Horrible grading for the group project. Even if you are rated highly you will end up losing at least 5-10 % of your mark purely from peer evaluation. If you can take 1301 with someone else then do it.

It is funny how a prof who teaches business ethics ends up having the most unethical grading system. What you say on the peer evaluation form worths more grades than your actual project. I don't know if this is the culture of Telfer or his teaching style only. But if other Telfer profs are like him, I am going back to grade 12 and apply for Ivey.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: The whole class was like a stage for him to show off his skills and talents. The use of a stupid peer evaluation system dropped my group grades down just because I didn't explain much on why I graded my peers 10/10. If I must have learned something in his class, it would be to comment on my team members in the same length as an essay in the future.

This Professor is a horrible grader, you would have the impression that he doesnt want you do to well. He uses the peer evaluation to deduct a big chunk of your mark and a lot of us have found that unfair. Indeed, if you have an average of 7/10 for the peer evaluation hell still find a way to deduct like +10% of your final group mark. AVOID HIM

Bad prof. Always talked about how low his rate my prof ratings were. Definitely makes you work for your grades- completing the work isn't enough and you have to go "above and beyond". Didn't open the textbook once, casebook wasn't important either so don't buy them. Uncompromising when it comes to assignments and is passive aggressive in emails.

The lad is passionate about the subject he is teaching, as you can tell from his limitless energy. But what frustrates me is his "Palmer supremacy" over exams, which are hard to prepare for them since textbook content is useless and most questions are from his random gibberish. I am knackered and gutted because this is my first in-person class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: john is a decent teacher but conveys the material in such a draining way. He always seems to be constantly going off on tangents that some how result in him talking about an accomplishment of his. Definitely an ego driven teacher and overall conveys a condescending tone. Half the time I find myself asking why Im attending the lectures in the first
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: The final was 100 long multiple choice questions in 2 hours like are you kidding me? I barely had time the read through the question I had to move on to the next one. Wants to trap his students, not help them.

I would rather go through the blood eagle process than take this profs class again. This geezer does not teach by the book, so it really adds extra pressure since there is no way that you can attend every lecture under the current situation. Midterm and final exams are just some made-up gibberish to mug everyone off so that u will respect PALMER.

Palmer likes to say that he's fair, but that is farcical. He lets his ego get in the way of being a good prof and he is condescending in emails. He sent an aggressive email to our class because people (understandably) left some bad reviews on rate my prof. He called the people who left these reviews "unethical" for making false claims.

I haven't gotten my final grade back yet because I don't want that to influence my review. All I wanna say is John Palm, if you're reading this (and I know you read your reviews), I wanna say thank you for being such a caring soul about mental health during these times that have been undoubtedly stressful for so many. This guy is a pure human being

A genuinely nice human being, but lets his emotions get in the way of teaching. Doesn't appreciate being emailed and is absolutely obsessed with the Respondus Lockdown browser; completely dismisses students wishes for privacy when it comes to Respondus and tried to force us into using it. He is knowledgeable of the material and lectures decent.

Had Prof Palmer before the COVID mess. I really wish all profs were as HUMAN as he is during online stuff. I'm in 3rd yr now, and looking back all these complaints I read are what ended up making him the BEST prof not the worst. You want a robot: take another prof. You want a caring, living, laughing human being: take Prof Palmer.

Avoid this prof if you can. This guy is terrible with the online technology and he makes the deliverables way harder than other classes. He also seems to talk more about his personal life than the actual course content.

The slowest grader at the University of Ottawa award goes to Johnny Palmer! Absolutely preposterous. He takes emails as personal attacks and avoids helping the student at all costs. He seemed like a great guy talking about playing cricket in the first week of classes, turns out he shouldn't even be a part-time prof, ridiculous. Avoid JOHN!

Professor Palmer is one of the best professor I have had during my time at UOTTAWA. He transformed my way of thinking into more creative ways to develop an argument. I don't have any thing bad to say about Prif Palmer because he treat all of us with respect during the lectures.

I spent 30 dollars buying a question booklet for practice so that I could master the class, but this prof gave us an exam that was totally imaginary and irrelevant. I am here to get a degree, not here to become a master HR professional. The midterm exam was a total trap that was designed to depress students. Please avoid him.

This professor brings good energy to his lectures and seems very kind however, I learned more about his family than the course itself. The midterm was challenging and his lectures were not helpful and did not prepare us. Your best bet is to focus on the textbook if you have him. Not to be rude but academically speaking, try and avoid.

Some people are so full of it. I was in the online Fall 2020 1301 class. Prof was 100% caring, responsive, clear on expectations. The only time he was a bit snippy was when 3 of you literally ganged up on him because he made a decision that was fair to EVERYONE, not just them. Some people just blame others.
Not even halfway into the term and he is my fave prof. Why have you business guys been keeping him to yourself???? Blew me away when he talked about his concern for our mental health. Dude is legit.

As much as I love John Palmer's personality, I wouldn't say he fits the job as a professor. He is always very talkative, chill, easy-going, and keep the class fun. Give lots of time for you to work on the class project, give help whenever needed. Would be a great TA that engage you into conversations, but talk too much off-topics in class.

If I could travel back to four months ago, I would never take this blokes class. His behaviour felt like he was high on something, which is a good thing since his unlimited energy certainly entertained me. But his exams and assignments were tough and irrelevant to the textbook. He might be good for physical classes, but he is certainly bad online.

Instead of hearing out students when they questioned him on stuff, he took many of it as a personal attack and seemed to want to make enemies out of students while claiming how unproblematic he is. I shied away from voicing some of my concerns directly to him because of the unhelpful/unfriendly answers other students received.

Very chill prof, he is actually interested in what he teaches and takes criticism constructively. He is very approachable and really gives good discussion in points given in chat. He understands students have other courses and is aware of busy workloads and tries to help students. I will see how the rest of the semester goes.

His efforts for the well-being of students at the minimum. He teaches part time, i felt like he doesnt take the job seriously. Not so caring to the students. The night before the final exam i realized i havent learned much in this course. Not Recommended.
It's clear that the good reviews are from John and not the students. Since this is my first review and there are several students with the same issue.

I sent him an e-mail asking a simple question & he replied rudely & implied I'm wasting his time. He said my e-mail was too long but it was 5 sentences including a polite intro & brief explanation of my question with some added context. He refused to look into my concern (which is fine) but he really made me feel badly for even having e-mailed him.

He is so chill, funny, and great prof! He is not stingy! He is straight to the point. U should read the module before lectures. His quizzes are fair. If u have a good teammate, ur assignments should be good. The final exam was harder. Its my fault; I didnt study the right things! So u should know a little about every concept (his notes, ppt, book).

The prof has great lectures. The con of the prof: do not have a great attitude toward students that especially have questions and problems about respondus. The exam is fair, if you listen to the lecture carefully, you can get a "B".We also get an individual assignment, you need to read extra content to answer some of the questions.
Professor Palmer is one of the most compassionate professors you'll encounter. His lectures are fun, and his assignments/final were fair! The course itself is very interesting and useful.
Very rude prof
please avoid him
He is the stingiest prof I have had. Please avoid at all costs.

Not sure how one person could hold so many grudges to bother leaving so many untrue 1 star reviews. Professor Palmer has been nothing but the kindest, most caring, and fair professor at Telfer. I've never had a prof who provides the best for students the way he does, I cant recommend him enough! If you see him available, TAKE HIM! You won't regret.

It is clear that the reviews preceding this have been written by 1 individual in an attempt to negatively impact Prof Palmers reputation. None of them are true. I have chosen John 3 times for courses, simply because he is an excellent professor with real life experience. He is engaging, knowledgeable, and above all fair. 5/5 without a doubt.
Hes okay but if you can take another prof
Snarky, rude, and self condescending when answering emails. Talks too much about personal life and marks harshly
Rudest prof I have ever had. DO NOT TAKE HIM!!
Snarky when answering emails and overall rude prof also marks harshly
Talks a lot about useless stuff and wastes your time. Save yourself and take someone else

I have never written any poor review for a professor before but I feel that I need to warn other students that Professor Palmer is someone you do NOT want to have. He is so rude when answering emails, he marks very harshly, he talks non-stop about his personal life and other stuff that no one cares about, and overall is an unnecessarily mean prof.

Prof. Palmer was awesome. He was a great introduction to University as a first-year. He cracks jokes and tells great stories relevant to the content. He doesn't have many assignments, but the ones he does give are A LOT with some group work. The exams weren't too bad and very much passable with the right amount of dedication. I would reccomend

Definitely one of my favourite profs so far. Many of my other profs made exams super hard this semester which took a huge toll on my grades and was not helpful, considering the challenges of online learning. This prof, however, made sure the exam was reasonable and fair. He is one of those profs that really care about the success of their students!
Very good energy, but does not give a lot of preparations. No exam review whatsoever, no practice exam or units of emphasis.

Amazing Professor and knows what he's talking about. He made sure to answer any questions outside of class and respected all of his students. He would make sure to have fun with the online classes and even though it was a 3 hour class I always looked forward to it. He told us what was expected and the due dates way ahead of time. Amazing Prof!!

Overall, his approach to teaching keeps students highly engaged and interested during lectures. His expectations are fair when it comes to grading, and is very understanding, considering the difficulties of online learning. Great professor to have for my first year course.

Great professor. You can really tell that he cares about his subject and his students. He takes time to answer questions and does it in a non-condescending way. He is a very fair grader, not too easy and not too hard. Would take classes from him again 10/10.

Prof gives amazing/engaging lectures, assigns fair/clear work, and is one of the most compassionate teachers I have ever met. He truly wants his students to succeed. Not only is he a good teacher, but he's also someone you can go to outside of class for a meaningful conversation. If ur reading this, thank you for getting me through a tough semester
One of the nicest profs I've had in Telfer so far. Adapted his lectures very well to online learning but i'd love to take some of his courses again in future years.

Professor Palmer is a terrific professor. Teaching a course based on business ethics, it is no doubt that this professor cares about his personal ethics. If you are ever unsure about something in the course material or the syllabus, reach out to him. He is very fair, takes the time to answer questions, and is very responsive.

Professor Palmer has been so excellent this semester! If you have to take ADM1301, I HIGHLY recommend taking it with him. He is an excellent, fair, and caring prof. I cannot recommend him enough, and I would absolutely take any courses with him in the future. He has done an excellent job throughout a difficult and unusual semester.

The class was quite good because there aren't many chapter readings and the work is mainly assignments. People found the individual report to be hard but if you follow the rubric closely you will get an easy A. Professor Palmer's lectures are really good and he answers all questions during class. You will have to use Respondus for online learning.

Prof Palmer was awesome, he is so kind, responsive, and his lectures are hilarious, fun and informative. He is one of the nicest profs I've had the privilege of having and I would totally take him again!

This professor was really good and he made the lectures interesting to watch while online. At the end of the course, he made a quiz to not use respondus on our exam, which most people didn't know about so they were mad about that, but not a big deal as we didn't end up using it anyways. Aside from that, decent teacher and interesting lectures.

John is a really good professor and one of my favorites. His class was made up of an individual assignment, and a group assignment, and a final. This was not decided by him, but I enjoyed writing a paper instead of a midterm. Yes, you had to read the content ahead of time welcome to uni, Finally the marks came late but this was out of his control!

Despite the content of his courses not necessarily being my passion, he is clearly very knowledgeable on his material and often pauses to ask if we're still following (giving you ample time to "raise your hand" and ask a question. I would not chose to re-take any classes, but I wouldn't mind getting this prof again :)

Professor Palmer was absolutely FANTASTIC. Great lectures, made it super easy to understand. Answered all questions comprehensively and respectfully. 4th year student at the time of writing this, Prof Palmer is EASILY in my top 3 favourite profs. HIGHLY RECOMEND!!

Not accessible outside of class. Assigns reports on material that he will teach AFTER the assignment due date. This means you need to read the entire textbook on your own within the first month so that you're able to do the first assignment. Does not provide timely feedback. We have 2 weeks left and haven't received a single mark back. Avoid.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Group projects', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: His lectures are good but he brings up content included on assignments after they are due and changes his mind last minute. He sometimes comes across as snarky when you email him a question.
His lectures are bang average, the only good thing about it is that he talks about the syllabus and brings up stuff that is about 30% assignments that are not on the syllabus.

Prof Palmer is not used to online education yet. He dose give amazing lectures for sure which makes me want to take his class again offline. During online classes, he's not accessible outside of class and not very caring. He gave a 15 pages essay instead of midterm for a first year class and the rubric for group project is not clear at all. Sad.

If you have to take ADM1301, I highly recommend taking it with him! He is an excellent professor, has great lectures, and especially out of all the professors this semester, gave a fair and manageable paper as a midterm. I am very happy that I switched into his class, and I would absolutely recommend taking any course with him!
Best professor I've had! He delivers amazing lectures that keep you interested. You can tell he really cares about his students. 10/10 recommend.

He is a wonderful prof. Cares a lot about his students and you can clearly see he likes his job. His lecture are interesting and super fun! But beware to do lots of work. His assignment are really demanding and will take lots of your time but he is clear about his expectation.
Very kind and understanding professor, does his best to help you succeed!
Palmer gives interesting lectures. However, he is extremely rude to his students and makes his course expectations very unclear.
BEST PROF YOU WILL HAVE
I went to one class and left early, never bought the textbook and never bothered to look at the class decks (around 70 slides each).

He is an amazing prof with lots of care for students. He showed care not only in students' scores but also in their future development and mental health. His lecture was interesting and always not up to 3 hrs. He was also my prof for the ADM3333 class. I would say he prefers to use group projects and short answer questions as evaluating criteria
Good prof, but the final was ridiculous.

This prof was the best in my whole 4 years of university! I'm very sad that I only met him in my last year. He is very genuine and understands the struggles of the students. He said to us that he isn't there to make us fail and I have never heard a prof say that before. His lectures are awesome with lots of examples and his exams are fair.

Honesty a sweetheart, although his tests are tricky. I advise going to the lectures as he gives hints to what will be tested (if he says he loves a topic, make note of this as it will probably be on the test). Some stuff on tests will only be talked about in class (not in slides or textbook). Does take attendance on rare occasions

His teaching skills are not questionable without a doubt, but his midterm and final were the hardest thing I have ever written since I came to this university. The prof needs to change the format and level of difficulty for this course's exams as it is impossible for a first-year student to answer such tough questions.

His lectures are great, he's extremely knowledgeable, and he makes a relatively boring course a tad more enjoyable with his lessons. BUT! His midterm and final exam are stupidly difficult, like unnecessarily so. Marking takes way too long and feedback is minimal. Also doesn't properly respond to emails or concerns in a timely manner.

John palmer is the sweetest prof ever, very caring ,very understanding of students' difficulties. Really easy grader and gives a lot of part marks even if you don't answer the question completely. The midterm was easy but the final was okay. He gives great examples an class and never lets you get bored in a 3 hour lecture. Just go for him.

The prof with no doubts is good at delivering a lecture. However, the midterm and final made me feel like I was taking a master degree class rather than the first-year class, they are definitely the hardest exams I have ever written so far.
You can tell that he is a prof with passion, but he makes the midterm of this pointless course way too hard than it is supposed to be.

He says the course is being rebuilt, which is good. It's the worst textbook in the world. He did add a lot of unique stuff - some of it challenging - and added good chunks of humour to make it palatable. He makes a bad course livable.

Alrite prof but nothing to write home about. I feel like I just learned more about his personal life than course material. He really has trouble staying on topic unfortunately. 3 hr lectures will have like 40 minutes of applicable information. Expectations for this course are fairly unclear throughout the course.

Overall great prof. Lectures tend to be a little boring due to the subject material. He tried really hard to make it less dull and tries to get the class to participate. Study the textbook and you will have no problem passing and doing well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I loved his 7-10!!!! My favourite course first year. You could tell that he really puts effort into every single lecture and you never feel like you are FORCING yourself to go, you'll go because you want to and take something out of everything that he says!

Funny, fair and communicates well. Some summer students don't care about class, then whine when they get bad marks. He told us up front that he'd give us 75% of needed material and text was important. Responds to emails quickly, and re-marks fairly. Best prof ever.
He is a good guy, though the lecture is extremely boring. I have to read all the chapters of the textbook for the final, while eventually felt like learning nothing.

Taking his 7-10 was the best choice I made in first year. The midterm was really hard but the final and group project went really well. Going to class and doing those weekly assignments are really important if you want an A. He is a super great prof and I highly recommend taking his class.
Funn y

he genuinely cares about his students and wants to them to do better. midterms and final were fair, the group project was a pain and the weekly assignments were an easy 10% if you did them correctly (also, dont buy the textbook) . overall, best first year prof i had and would take him again. Also, he loves answering students questions, so ask!

I really enjoyed professor Palmer's style, he put issues to us in a way I could understand and cared about the classes success without babying or going soft on those who didnt try. Favourite class of the semester when I expected to hate it! Legend!

Has an awkward comedy routine whivh made his 3 hour class more bearable. Constantly begins and encourages class participation, and stopped several kids from taking the final for not showing up to too many classes. Posts everything online. Overall great prof.

The course content is an especially steep curve, especially for me leading up to the midterm which affected my view on the course. I didn't like the course, but he seemed to engage in discussions in where to improve the course and had some insightful discussions too. Be ready to work on assignments though!

Palmer knows what he is talking about. He relates the majority of material to experiences and events in the real world. Plamer makes the boring material lively and interesting, making his lectures very enjoyable. Always answers questions and has class discussions. Genuinly cares about his students and improving others. Wonderful Prof!

John was a great prof, mid term multiple choice were a bit tough but he easied them up on the final. Made a 3 hour lecture tolerable. Lots of content of in class is tested so make sure you attend. The weekly assignments are just easy grades if you complete them. Overall great class

Great prof, loves teaching and cares about his students. Be careful to read textbook material in depth though... His lectures don't cover everything and test banks won't save you for short-answer and case study questions in the final. Don't hesitate to speak with him about any concerns you have, lectures are lots of fun.
Class context is boring but prof is not bad. Midterm is hard and all points are important, you have to review and try to memorize the textbook if you want to get good mark

Comes prepared to class and keeps the class engaged. Seems very knowledge, especially public sector HR. One thing that Professor Palmer could learn from was announcing the exam format more clearly. He changed the midterm format 3 times before the exam (from multiple choice only to chap1-8 to chap1-7) and we had do do a second part for the midterm..

Professor Palmer is extremely knowledgeable in many areas of business. Most of all, he is not a condescending professor who is only in it for the research. Palmer truly cares about his students, reputation, grades, and most of all learning. By far the best professor of my undergrad even with a mediocre course

Seriously the best prof I've had in 4 years at Telfer. He's super open and has discussions in class that are funny but relevant and keep you engaged. Midterms + final are super fair and reflections take minimal time to complete. Would take several other classes with him if I were an HR student.
Pretty boring subject but a good prof and makes the class interesting. Tests were fairly easy and its not hard to get a good mark

There are lots of little assignments to keep you busy. There are reflections due almost every week or so, as well as a group assignment. 2 midterms and a final. He is a knowledge prof that cares about his students. I really liked him.
Great Prof, definitely recommend him if you are taking MIS. Funny, passionate and clear criterias for the class. The book and attendance is a must. Loved this course because of him.

Well, he tried. Had him for MIS in the summer, and he tried to get the class to discuss things, but failed. Our fault not his. At least made enough jokes so that the summer wasn't a write off. Seems better than most profs.

Great professor, he is passionate, goofy and very engaging. He explains the content clearly. One down fall is the lack of time we had for in class case studies, but it is manageable. He also cares for his students and wants us to pass.

LOVE LOVE LOVE john palmer. literally my favorite prof at uottawa. he is extremely helpful and clear with his expectations and his projects and tests all completely reflect what is done in class- he does a great job of prepping you for your tests and always offers extra help. Hes got a lot of great experience which he regularly applies in lectures

Professor Palmer was simply AMAZING ! He explained the material thoroughly and provides the students with many examples and tried really hard to answer your questions. He is always available and is reliable. I loved this class so much and his teachings ! Lots of group discussions. His exam really reflected what was being taught in class, easy A+ !

He's a little bit of a know it all and full of himself. Although I may not be fond of this professor his lectures are engaging and useful, especially when you take into account the course material that he is teaching.

Amazing professor I would definitely take any of his courses again. Interactive teaching style, truly cares about his students and the subject matter at hand. Great guy in general, believed in what he was teaching, and great at responding to any concerns you may have. Not an easy class, but it was far and away my favourite class of the semester. :)

Amazing prof! By far my favourite one from this semester! Makes boring 3 hour lectures really interactive and he is always willing to listen to everyones opinions. Highly recommend him! Although, to do well you must attend every lecture, read the text book and study hard. Exams were tough!

Great prof! very animated. Great feedback on assignments. A lot of memorization for the exams. Though mid-term. Group project can turn sour with the team. He is happy to help, probably the most approachable prof you will know. He is funny and very interactive with the class, even with 160 students.

Wow! Amazing Prof! If you have the option to take his class, please do! He is so helpful and truly cares about his students. He answers emails quickly and grades everything quickly. He is very clear on what he expects and if you are not understanding something he is more than happy to help. Midterm was difficult.

Mr Palmer was great! He is great with blackboard and updates it regularly, the assignments get graded fairly quickly, he is clear on what he wants and explains everything really well. Great at answering emails and reassuring students about concerns. Overall he was an amazing prof. The midterm was really tough but he tries to prepare the students.

Fantastic prof! I had him twice now and would jump at the chance to have him again. He makes dry, technical content relevant and very clear and throws in some jokes or stories to help keep the mood light. There are a lot of group case studies though and his exams are tough but if you study hard (book + lec. notes) and have a good group, you're set.

Amazing professor, midterms and final are tough. Need to read the slides and textbook to do well. make sure you do well on group projects. Had him for 3 hours and loved every class. Don't be afraid to talk to him, he loves talking to students.

This class can be challenging if you do not have a tech background. The material can be hard to understand and I don't believe the prof explained it very well. This prof goes on long tangents and I found his lectures really boring.  The exams are tough so if you want to do well, make sure you study hard.

John Palmer was an angel sent from above for clarity of his expectations and somehow kept his students coming back for more(maybe it was the in-class cases everyday of the semester ;). He'll grade you easy for everything barring the midterm and finals! Also don't forget NUMBER ONE GEEK IN UOTTAWA :)

This class was odd: not the prof I signed up for. He started first lecture on ethics and culture - WHY? But by the end (especially final lecture) it was clear he cared not only about the topic, and helping us learn and pass, but also about us as people. I would sign up for anything with his name on it! uOttawa needs more like him!

This prof is simply amazing. He makes classes so enjoyable for a course that you could easily hate. He was always there for office hours and answers emails. Extremely nice and funny. Would definitely recommend him for MIS.

Got him for 2372 but have not seen any ratings for him in this.  Maybe its his first time  Seems to know the topic and can be funny in class.  Lots of group assignments but that seems to be same across all sections of the class. Tries to get class involved. Will see how the term goes fingers crossed.

This professor has the hardest midterms(If you want a good mark, I wouldn't take this class) but the final is easy. No clue what he wants from you, but he is way more interesting to listen to than the other prof that teaches this course.You can tell he enjoys teaching this class. You gain some and you lose some.

Made a dull course interesting. Knows some pretty cool people as well, had some very interesting people come and do presentations. Always there for students 100% of the time, always has office hours, very nice to talk to. You'll have to do a fair amount of work. Very fair marker, Highly recommended.
Pretty good professor, teaches well and has a very interactive class. Midterm and quizzes are hard, so you'll need to study hard for them. Highest mark in the class going into the final was an 86%.
hard midterm. is nice and willing to help.

Very nice teacher! He wants to see his students do well and is always willing to help.  He is available all the time for office hours and actually treats you like a person not just another student.  His midterm and quizzes are a bit difficult  you really need to know your stuff to do well. Boring topic but he tries to make it interesting.
not sure what class others are in cos we knew almost exactly what was on mid-term and tests. he's usually funny, always has office hours. far better than i was afraid of in a first year course
midterm was very time consuming, have to know everything inside out to complete it if you want a decent mark

Worst class ever in first year! First time ever teaching and he was horrible! Although he was a nice person, his quizzes and midterms were ridiculous. Does not specify what's on it, tells us its easy and it ends up being extremely hard.  Midterm was all writing, very very long and the average was so low. I would not recommend this prof to anyone!
tough but fair. more lively than expected for a dull course.
